# Run the Server Locally

Learn how to build dependencies, configure Arc, and run the local server workflow.

@Tutorial(time: 12) {
    @Intro(title: "Run the Server Locally") {
        This tutorial walks you through building the required tooling, starting Arc, and verifying that static sites and services are running correctly.
    }

    @Section(title: "Prerequisites") {
        @ContentAndMedia {
            Make sure you have the Swift toolchain installed and the repo cloned with submodules initialized.

````sh
git submodule update --init --recursive
swift --version
````
        }
    }

    @Section(title: "Build Required Tooling") {
        @ContentAndMedia {
            Arc and WebUI live in `tooling/`. Build them once before running the server.

````sh
cd tooling/arc && swift build -c release
cd ../web-ui && swift build -c release
````
        }
    }

    @Section(title: "Configure Arc") {
        @ContentAndMedia {
            Arc reads configuration from `Arc.swift` at the repo root. Ensure your sites and services are listed with proper domains, ports, and paths.

            Example structure for a static page:

````swift
.page(
    name: "portfolio",
    domain: "portfolio.localhost",
    outputPath: "sites/portfolio/.output"
)
````

            Example structure for a service:

````swift
.service(
    name: "guest-list",
    domain: "guest-list.localhost",
    port: 8000,
    process: .process(
        workingDir: "sites/guest-list/Web/",
        executable: ".build/arm64-apple-macosx/release/GuestListWeb"
    )
)
````
        }
    }

    @Section(title: "Build Projects") {
        @ContentAndMedia {
            Build service binaries and generate static sites.

            Build a service:

````sh
cd sites/guest-list/Web
swift build -c release
````

            Generate a static site:

````sh
cd sites/portfolio
swift run
````
        }
    }

    @Section(title: "Run Arc") {
        @ContentAndMedia {
            Start the server from the repo root.

````sh
arc run
````

            If `arc` is not on your PATH, run the binary directly or add it to PATH. Use the path that matches your machineâ€™s architecture:

````sh
./tooling/arc/.build/arm64-apple-macosx/release/arc
./tooling/arc/.build/x86_64-apple-macosx/release/arc
````

            Use these commands as needed:

            - `arc run --background`
            - `arc status`
            - `arc logs`
            - `arc stop`
        }
    }

    @Section(title: "Verify Locally") {
        @ContentAndMedia {
            After Arc starts, open the configured domains in your browser. Static sites should resolve immediately, and services should respond once their binaries are running.

            If you change configuration in `Arc.swift`, Arc reloads automatically.
            If you rebuild a service binary or regenerate a static site, Arc updates automatically.
        }
    }
}
